'''rommap''' - Template for ROM map tables on games.darkrepos.com

==Description==

This template creates standardized ROM map tables documenting the memory layout of game ROMs. It supports both file offsets and CPU addresses, with optional bank information.

==Usage==

===Basic Usage===
<pre>
{{rommap}}
</pre>

===With Parameters===
<pre>
{{rommap
| platform = NES
| header_size = 16
| bank_size = 16384
| description = Custom description text
}}
</pre>

==Parameters==

{| class="wikitable"
|-
! Parameter !! Required !! Default !! Description
|-
| platform || No || — || Platform name (NES, SNES, GBA) - adds platform-specific column headers
|-
| header_size || No || — || ROM header size in bytes (e.g., 16 for iNES header)
|-
| bank_size || No || — || Bank size in bytes for calculating addresses
|-
| description || No || (standard text) || Custom description for the page
|}

==Table Columns==

The generated table includes these columns:
* '''Offset''' - File offset (hex)
* '''Address''' - CPU/PRG address (platform-dependent)
* '''Length''' - Data size in bytes
* '''Bank''' - Bank number (if applicable)
* '''Description''' - What the data contains

==Example Output==

{{rommap|platform=NES|header_size=16}}

| $00010 || $8000 || $4000 || 00 || PRG Bank 0 - Game initialization
|-
| $04010 || $8000 || $4000 || 01 || PRG Bank 1 - Overworld code
|-
|}

==Best Practices==

* Always document both file offset and CPU address when possible
* Note if offset includes header (file offset) vs excludes header (ROM offset)
* Group related entries with comments
* Link to sub-pages for large data structures

